...)<br><br>My question is, what would be a good system to put in place to govern the allocation of these often contested pieces so I don't lose members and or foster bad feelings amongst the ranks.<br><br>As guild leader, I want to see the guild do well and build up it's equipment, and I have a plan that I'm trying to put in place, which in it's first stages, simply calls for the development of our core tanks.  It is my belief that outfitting our tanks with the best equipment within our reach will make the biggest impact on our guild in the short term.  It will also, in my belief, facilitate the outfitting of the rest of the guild since we will (hopefully) have the tankage to confront bigger and badder mobs successfully.<br><br>Anyway, I was just throwing this out in the hopes that someone may be able to help me with some sort of looting scheme that will keep the majority of my peeps happy (yes, I do realize that I won't be able to make EVERYONE happy).<br><br>Thank you in advance,<br> <p><center>Morit ~52nd Wanderer ~ Guild Leader ~ <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/bforsakenlords>Forsaken Lords</a></center><br><center><img src="http://pages.sbcglobal.net/jaykelly/_uimages/MoritSig.jpg"></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/umusemischiefmaker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Muse Mischiefmaker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bored Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 351<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/25/02 12:07:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1394.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.eqcompanions.com/images/characters/Muse/musekiss.jpg height=171 width=137></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Looting system...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> As guild leader, I want to see the guild do well and build up it's equipment, and I have a plan that I'm trying to put in place, which in it's first stages, simply calls for the development of our core tanks. It is my belief that outfitting our tanks with the best equipment within our reach will make the biggest impact on our guild in the short term. It will also, in my belief, facilitate the outfitting of the rest of the guild since we will (hopefully) have the tankage to confront bigger and badder mobs successfully.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>Totally the way to go, as long as you can balance it with the other classes as well as making it known to your guild how much it will help <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> them</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> in the long run by giving your main warrior a 50ac breastplate before the bards of the guild.<br><br>Personally, I prefer attendance-based looting to /random. Random is nice and lets everyone get a chance at uber items, but it has the potential to make a guild stagnant and cause you to take longer to get to the next &quot;stage&quot; of the game. (I mean, ACK, what if the ranger that shows for 2 months per raid gets that amazing haste item over a melee that is at every raid you schedule? That doesn't help the guild much as a whole...)<br><br>My 2cp. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><b><a href="http://darkmask.windsofstorm.net/images/ladies/fullsize/muse.jpg">Muse</a> &lt;<a href="http://www.the-elitists.com">Elitists and Vagrants</a>><br><a href="http://www.thetribunal.org">The Tribunal Server</a><br><font size="1"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=2399">My Magelo Profile</a></font></b>