i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/uelcheproudfoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elche Proudfoot</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mmmmm lobster</span><br>  Posts: 560<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/25/02 12:40:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1394.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://images.about.com/specials/service/promotion/sod/male_lead_stealer/josh_ryan_evans.jpg width=129 height=163></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Looting system...</span><hr size=1> Honestly, sometimes I think the best loot system is the one where the officers just hand it out to those who they think should get it. <br><br>but thats just my opinion and not that of my guild <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br><br> <p><font size="-2" face="verdana">Elche Proudfoot<BR><b>Founder and Chief Mystic</font><br><font color=red size="-2" face="verdana"> Shining Path</FONT></b> </FONT><BR><font color=black size=-1><I>And then she got out of the car and commenced a whooping on me,'" the victim said</i></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/umoritthedruid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Morit The Druid</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lurker</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/25/02 12:45:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1394.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Looting system...</span><hr size=1> Well, I've known for some time that no matter what you do in your capacity as guild leader, there will always be someone who will not like it.  That's a fact and something I've come to accept and deal with (though sometimes it's hard!).<br><br>A little history: Forsaken Lords was started by a group of friends who left Remnants some months back.  Instead of scattering to the 4 winds, we decided to create our own guild and remain together.  Amazingly, many of our founding members are still with the guild despite head hunting by some of the bigger guilds.  Sorta tells ya what sort of folks we have here.  The ex-Rems, and many of our new additions are all very excellent people who are pretty open to sacrifice and helping their fellow guild members out.  We currently number around 55 to 60 people with an average level range of mid 40's to mid 50's.<br><br>My problem is that I don't want to seem partial in any way towards one member or another.  <br><br>If I come up with a system that basically leaves it up to the officers to decide who gets what based on merit, sort of as rewards, I will undoubtedly make some peeps angry and possibly alienate them because of a perception of favoritism.<br><br>If I come up with a &quot;point&quot; system, I'd first have to set up a &quot;point&quot; system and assign values for certain deeds.  The problem with this is that regardless of what the points &quot;say&quot;, someone will undoubtedly want to throw &quot;mitigating circumstances&quot; in as to why they should get the item vs. so and so because... blah.. blah...  and I'd be back to justifying the reason behind the decision to award this person the item.  This system is perhaps the easiset to use when defending an award.  The &quot;numbers&quot; don't lie...<br><br>If I don't have a system and just let the dice decide who gets what when, we will have angry &quot;bad luck&quot; players, or angry &quot;im always at raids but so and so gets the item on his first raid&quot; people to deal with.  And of course the guild will sort of evolve haphazardly with no real stratgey behind it.  Not my best option by far.<br><br>So I guess what I'm looking for are examples of some of the looting schemes you guys use?  But I also greatly appreciate all the responses made here.<br><br><br> <p><center>Morit ~52nd Wanderer ~ Guild Leader ~ <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/bforsakenlords>Forsaken Lords</a></center><br><center><img src="http://pages.sbcglobal.net/jaykelly/_uimages/MoritSig.jpg"></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/uelcheproudfoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elche Proudfoot</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mmmmm lobster</span><br>  Posts: 561<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/25/02 1:16:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1394.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://images.about.com/specials/service/promotion/sod/male_lead_stealer/josh_ryan_evans.jpg width=129 height=163></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Looting system...</span><hr size=1> hey morit. <br><br>drop me a line if you want<br><br><!--EZCODE MAIL START--><a href="mailto: shining_path@hexenworld.com"> shining_path@hexenworld.com</a><!--EZCODE MAIL END--><br><br>I have wrestled with loot systems for far too llng <p><font size="-2" face="verdana">Elche Proudfoot<BR><b>Founder and Chief Mystic</font><br><font color=red size="-2" face="verdana"> Shining Path</FONT></b> </FONT><BR><font color=black size=-1><I>And then she got out of the car and commenced a whooping on me,'" the victim said</i></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/umakino.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Makino</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Flowers Before Boys</span><br>  Posts: 93<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/25/02 1:20:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1394.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Looting system...</span><hr size=1> Have the officers decide loot.  Of course people will bitch and moan, but as has been said before, no system is perfect.  Also, officers can get the right people, who you know will stay with your guild and help you better in the long run the gear they need to be the most effective.   If you leave it up to the dice, you will see nothing but lame asses get valuable gear.  Always bear in mind, not all guildmembers are created equal.  There are those who are more vaulable to your long term success.  You can't treat your guild like a democracy when it comes to loot and expect to see tangible results anytime soon.  As Muse said, this will bog down your guild a lot.<br><br>As for the point system, either create a database to track all the crap or don't even bother because you'll be spending more time just calculating all that junk out rather than actually playing. <p><hr>Insert Cool Makino Picture Here!<br>Makino Tsukushi<br>Flowers Before Boys<br>The Companions<br>The Tribunal</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/uladidahohum.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ladida Hohum</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Hey baby...<br>Ever done it in a drawer?</span><br>  Posts: 1741<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/25/02 1:51:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1394.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://ladida5000.homestead.com/files/ladidadwarf3.jpg height=147 width=132></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Looting system...</span><hr size=1> Tanje, you are so wrong. There is a perfect looting system. It is one that I devised for CRoN, but unfortunately never went into effect do to those racist bastards on the naming committee.<br><br>1) Have everyone who wants an item, say in shout, “NICE!” (WOW! is also acceptable, but it must be in all caps and include at least one exclamation mark).<br><br>2) Then, after enough time so that enough people can voice that they want it, you say in shout, “let the perfect loot system begin!”<br><br>3) Then everyone starts yelling about how they deserve it more than others, and how so and so is the biggest greedy loot whore, etc. Even people who are not up for it can rag on others or say how so and so needs that item more or deserves it more. (This lasts for 4 mins.)<br><br>4) People who originally wanted the item may be able to back down if they want to if the insults get to hard or they themselves see that someone else may deserve it more. To drop out of contention, all you have to say is, “Jesus. It is just a fucking item,” “You guys take this game waaay to seriously,” or “Fuck it, I don’t want it anymore.”<br><br>5) At the end of the 4 mins, if there is only one person left, then they get the item. If not, then Catch 84 is put into effect.<br><br>Catch 84: Guildleader roles a number between 1 and 100. If the number is 1 – 30, then the raid leader loots the item and may destroy it or just tell everyone he did. If the number is 31-70, then it goes to the person who the raid leader thought was the best in insults and reasoning. The losers of the Rule 84, have to remove their pants or greaves for the remainder of the raid unless later they loot greaves or pants later on and can then wear those. <p><BR><B><FONT color="gold">Ladida Hohum<BR>Vicar of The Tribunal Ser